content.text:
The `switch-case` structure evaluates a variable and executes the matching `case` block. The syntax is:
```c
switch (variable) {
  case value1:
    // Code runs if variable == value1
    break;
  case value2:
    // Code runs if variable == value2
    break;
  default:
    // Code runs if no case matches
}
```
- **`switch (variable)`**: Specifies the variable to check (usually `int` or `char`).
- **`case value`**: Compares the variable to a specific value. If it matches, this block runs.
- **`break`**: Stops the `switch` from continuing to the next `case`. Without it, subsequent cases will also run (called 'fall-through').
- **`default`**: Runs if no `case` matches (optional).

